gomodel:SYNGO_5453  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1: NCKX2 (SLC24A2) interacts with KIF21A in yeast two-hybrid and immunoprecipitation assays.\n\nFigure 2c,d: \"We performed immunocytochemistry on cultured hippocampal neurons expressing FLAG-KIF21A. Triple immunostaining with anti-FLAG, anti-NCKX2ext and anti-NF-H revealed that endogenous NCKX2 was colocalized with FLAG-KIF21A at the axon\"\n\nFigure 2g: \"The line profiles of NCKX2 (green) and FLAG-KIF21A (red) fluorescence intensities as well as the PDM image demonstrate that the NCKX2/FLAG-KIF21A complexes are localized in puncta along the axon fiber and in the axon terminal\"\n\nFigure 3: Axonal transport of NCKX2 is mediated by KIF21A.\n\nFigure 4: Knockdown of KIF21A abolishes the axonal transport of NCKX2.\n\nFigure 5: Knockdown of KIF21A alters calcium kinetics at the axon terminal.. Experimental description: M&M: \"In brief, 2 weeks before neuronal culture, astrocytes were obtained by passing a cortical cell suspension from postnatal day 1 (P1) Sprague Dawley (SD) rat of either sex through a cell strainer (40 μm mesh; Falcon; BD Biosciences Discovery Labware), and then cultured\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-17" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5453" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

